      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Justification provided for continuum mechanics assumptions, contact formulation, and omission of secondary geometric features; sensitivity of QoIs to model form choices documented.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic titanium alloy constitutive model justified by experimental stress-strain data showing elastic behavior below yield. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) selected based on literature values for Ti-Ti interfaces as discussed in related biomechanical literature. Cannulation omitted by design (non-cannulated device). Model form sensitivity study showed <3% QoI variation across plausible friction coefficient range 0.15–0.30. Gradation 3 satisfied."
