      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Multiple test conditions spanning the COU loading envelope; environmental conditions (temperature, humidity) documented and controlled.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single load configuration (ASTM F1717 standard geometry) at ambient laboratory conditions. While temperature and humidity were logged, only one mechanical test condition was employed. This limits achieved level to Gradation 2, below the required Gradation 3. This gap is acknowledged and accepted given that the ASTM F1717 condition is the regulatory standard condition and no clinical loading scenario outside this envelope is claimed in the COU."
    },
    {
